# Low-Cost Hearing Aid Using Arduino
## Team  
**Students**: Mohamed Elmogtaba, Adam Hamid Mohamed Elzein, Ibrahim Sami Bukhari  
**Supervisor**: Dr. Abdul Razzaq  

## 📌 Introduction  
Over 430 million people suffer disabling hearing loss (WHO). Commercial hearing aids cost $1,000-$4,000, making them inaccessible in developing regions. This project designs a functional alternative under $20 using Arduino.  

## 🎯 Objectives  
1. Develop hearing aid prototype with Arduino Nano  
2. Implement noise filtering algorithms  
3. Achieve production cost < $20  
4. Test with hearing-impaired users  

## ⚙️ Hardware Components  
| Component      | Cost  |  
|----------------|-------|  
| Arduino Nano   | $3.50 |  
| MAX9814 Mic    | $2.80 |  
| PAM8403 Amp    | $1.20 |  
| Li-ion Battery | $2.50 |  
| **Total**      | **$10.00** |  

